Surface of capitulum and stalk contains 6-, 7- and 8-radiate capstans (
Fig. 8D–E
); colony interior contains long, slender needles with a smooth median part and spiny trihedral ends. The interior needles, up to 
0.6 mm
long (
Fig. 8F
), have a smooth cylindrical median part, but trihedral ends. Each ridge at the needle end bears spines or dents (
Fig. 8G
).
